cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.RO, cs.MM 

This paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it deals with the detection and classification of small-sized vehicles in aerial scenes. It also involves the creation of a new airborne image dataset for experiments. Additionally, the use of a neural network for object detection and classification suggests that it may also belong to the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. The resource constraints of unmanned aerial vehicles (UAVs) suggest that it may also belong to the robotics (cs.RO) sub-category. Finally, the use of image datasets and the evaluation of performance metrics suggest that it may also belong to the multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category.
